:H2.TO
:XMP.
Format&gml. &gml.TO [compact].
         <recipient lines>
:eXMP.
:I2 refid='gtto'.gtto
:P.
The optional :HP2.&gml.to:eHP2. tag starts an address entity.
Each line following the tag will be a line in the address of
the letter recipient.
The first GML tag encountered will terminate the TO address.
:P.
The optional attribute :HP2.compact:eHP2. will suppress the
printing of blank lines in the address.
The option is most useful when printing form letters from
a database which contains some empty fields.
